      • showInProgressButton

        public void showInProgressButton()
        Method called when pressing the showInProgress button in the GUI. Updates the booking list to show all booking In progress, disables the showInProgressButton, and changes the text on the check-in button to Check out.

      • showBookedButton

        public void showBookedButton()
        Method called when pressing the showBooked button in the GUI. Updates the booking list to show all booking In progress, disables the showBooked button, and changes the text on the check-in button to Check in.

      • guestInformationButton

        public void guestInformationButton()
                            throws java.io.IOException
        Method called when pressing the guest information button in the GUI. Opens a window containing the guest information for the selected booking, which will allow the receptionist to make changes to the personal information of the guest.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • roomInformationButton

        public void roomInformationButton()
                           throws java.io.IOException
        Method called when pressing the room information button in the GUI. Opens a window containing the booking information for the selected booking, which will allow the receptionist to make changes to the booking or cancel it.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • checkInButton

        public void checkInButton()
        Method called when clicking the check in (or check out) button with a booking selected. creates a pop up window containing information about the costumer, and gives the ability to either confirm or go back. If confirm is choosen, the processBooking method in the viewModel is called.

      • mainMenuButtonClicked

        public void mainMenuButtonClicked()
        Method used when the Menu button is clicked in the window. It opens UserLoginMainView.
